Classroom Attention & Feedback Analyzer ER Diagram

This is a placeholder text file with .png extension.
Use this structure to draw the actual ER diagram in a tool like draw.io:

Entities:
- User (id, email, passwordHash, name, role, anonymousCode, createdAt, updatedAt)
- Class (id, name, subject, teacherId, createdAt, updatedAt)
- ClassEnrollment (id, classId, studentId, createdAt)
- Session (id, classId, startsAt, endsAt, attendanceClosesAt, createdAt)
- Attendance (id, sessionId, studentId, markedAt)
- Poll (id, sessionId, teacherId, question, isActive, createdAt)
- PollOption (id, pollId, text)
- PollResponse (id, pollId, optionId, studentId, createdAt)
- Doubt (id, sessionId, studentId, content, isResolved, createdAt)
- Feedback (id, sessionId, studentId, rating, comment, createdAt)
- Report (id, classId, sessionId, teacherId, generatedAt, averageRating, totalFeedback, totalAttendance, bonusAmount)
- Bonus (id, teacherId, sessionId, amount, status, createdAt)

Key relationships:
- User 1-N Class (teacher -> classes)
- User 1-N ClassEnrollment (student enrollments)
- Class 1-N Session
- Session 1-N Attendance
- Session 1-N Poll
- Poll 1-N PollOption
- Poll 1-N PollResponse
- Session 1-N Doubt
- Session 1-N Feedback
- Class / Session / User (teacher) 1-N Report
- User (teacher) 1-N Bonus

Anonymity:
- Students are represented only by User.id and anonymousCode; admin/teacher reports never expose email/name for role=STUDENT.

